    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3867183259" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3867183259" />
    <a title="Kathryn Bashaar" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/994755-kathryn-bashaar"><img alt="Kathryn Bashaar" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1600110280p2/994755.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3867183259?book_show_action=true">Mar 01, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathryn Bashaar" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathryn Bashaar" href="/user/show/994755-kathryn-bashaar">Kathryn Bashaar</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3867183259" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6815556750077434756">I&apos;ve kept a journal almost daily since I was 11 years old. So I know a little about journaling, and am thinking of developing a course and maybe writing about about keeping a journal.<br/><br/>In the interest of that, I&apos;ve decided to start reading other&apos;s journals, especially writers journals. I like Anne Lamott, so I started with this classic 1980s journal of her son Sam&apos;s first year of life.<br/><br/>As always, Lamott is very open about her flaws and insecurities, which makes this journal very relatable. She had </span>
  <span id="freeText6815556750077434756" style="display:none">I've kept a journal almost daily since I was 11 years old. So I know a little about journaling, and am thinking of developing a course and maybe writing about about keeping a journal.<br /><br />In the interest of that, I've decided to start reading other's journals, especially writers journals. I like Anne Lamott, so I started with this classic 1980s journal of her son Sam's first year of life.<br /><br />As always, Lamott is very open about her flaws and insecurities, which makes this journal very relatable. She had good days and bad days. She loved her baby every minute, but that doesn't mean she never got frustrated, and never felt desperate for one minute to herself or one decent night's sleep. <br /><br />I think this was a good book for its time. It was written back when all of us Boomers were having babies and were completely obsessed with ourselves and our babies. Lamott's honesty is always refreshing, and she comes up with clever, humorous descriptions for baby behavior. Example: when he first starts crawling, he looks "like a Komodo dragon." <br /><br />But I don't feel that this book has aged well, thirty years later. And Lamott had so much help from family and friends that some of her complaining seemed whiny to me. It actually sounded to me like she got out way more in Sam's first year than I did in my babies' first years - and I had a husband. Also, seriously, you DIDN'T GET A CHANCE TO BRUSH YOUR TEETH? Are you kidding me? Put the baby down for two minutes. He won't die. I know that sounds mean. But I guess I read all the books about how hard a baby's first year is back in the 80s when I had babies, and it's just not fresh any more. P.S. I didn't think it was that hard. It was exhausting, and some of the MOMENTS were awful, but overall I was very happy when I had little babies. <br /><br />Like my reviews? Check out my blog at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.kathrynbashaar.com/blog/">http://www.kathrynbashaar.com/blog/</a><br />Author of The Saints Mistress <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://camcatbooks.com/Books/T/The-Saint-s-Mistress">https://camcatbooks.com/Books/T/The-S...</a><br /><br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="6815556750077434756" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3867183259">
  <td colspan="2">
